    "index_reference": "acbor",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>ACBOR</h1><ol><li><p>The father of Baal-hanan, king of Edom, who ruled before the establishment of Israel’s kingdom (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen36:38-Gen36:39\">Genesis 36:38</a><span>–</span><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen36:38-Gen36:39\">39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr1:49\">1&nbsp;Chronicles 1:49</a>).</p></li><li><p>Micaiah’s son, a courtier (companion that worked in a king&apos;s court) of King Josiah of the southern kingdom of Judah. Josiah sent Acbor to ask Huldah, the prophetess, about the newly found Book of the Law (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:12-2Kgs22:14\">2&nbsp;Kings 22:12</a><span>–</span><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:12-2Kgs22:14\">14</a>). Acbor is also called Abdon, son of Micah (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:20\">2&nbsp;Chronicles 34:20</a>). He&nbsp;was the father of Elnathan (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer26:22\">Jeremiah 26:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:12\">36:12</a>).</p></li></ol>",
